article.headline: Oregon State 65, Washington State 55
article.story:
CORVALLIS, Ore. (AP) -- Brina Chaney had 13 points and seven
rebounds as Oregon State defeated Washington State 65-55 Saturday
night.

Bianca McCall scored 19 points to lead the Cougars, who have
lost 15 of their last 16 games.

Shannon Howell had 10 points for the Beavers (14-9, 8-6 Pac-10).
Leilani Estavan and Anita Rivera added nine.

Charmaine Jones scored 12 for the Cougars (5-19,1-14), whose
only conference win was over California.

Washington State led 17-13 early on, but the Beavers went on a
11-0 run to make it 24-17 at 5:12. The Beavers led 31-24 at
halftime.

The Cougars went on a 9-0 run to open up the second half and
took a 33-31 lead at 17:15. But Oregon State quickly recaptured the
lead when Mandy Close hit a 3-pointer at 12:55 to make it 44-39.
The Beavers' lead opened to 12 when Rivera hit two free throws,
making it 57-45 at 4:37.

Freshman Kate Benz had nine points and 11 rebounds for
Washington State. The Cougars shot just 33 percent for the game,
including 2-of-20 on 3s.

Oregon State was 17-of-17 from the free throw line.
